From 94213059f7c7a574624e10ca4489220f415a883f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vincenzo Grimaldi <vince.ceccarelli@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 03:39:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(ux): auto-hide header + unified section typography +
 alignment
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

HEADER — hide on scroll down, reveal on scroll up
- New useHideOnScroll hook (rAF-throttled, passive listener, 6px
  dead-zone to avoid flicker; always visible near top of page)
- Header (top utility bar + nav) is now one fixed group that translates
  with transform — the page NEVER shifts down or 'jumps'; content flow
  is unaffected because a spacer reserves the header height
  (h-20 mobile / h-[116px] desktop with utility bar)
- Stays visible while the mobile menu is open
- Removed redundant hero pt-16 now that the spacer handles offset

TYPOGRAPHY — one consistent system everywhere
- New SectionHeading component: single eyebrow + title pattern, one
  responsive type scale (text-3xl -> md:text-4xl), tracking-tighter,
  serif display, left-aligned by default
- Homepage sections (Soluciones por sector, Productos, Servicios, Por
  qué elegirnos) migrated to it and left-aligned consistently
- Dark/green focal bands (Compromiso, ¿Listo?) use the same component
  with align=center + tone=light so their scale matches the rest
- Eyebrows normalized to sentence case + tracking-[0.15em] across all
  pages (were tracking-[2px]/[2.5px]/[3px], mixed ALL-CAPS)

Verified: next build green (21 pages), tsc clean, runtime smoke test
confirms spacer + unified headings render, all routes 200.
